						<summary>

						<p>In the same place as above.</p>						

						<p>This inscription in modern characters, engraved in continuation of No. 33 above is dated Āṅgīrasa, Āṉi 9. It seems to record the authorisation, by the trustees, etc., of the temple of Subrahmaṇya at Kuṇṇakkuḍi, for the payment of one <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> by each family residing in the village Naḍuvakkōṭṭai belonging to the deity probably for the repairs etc., of the temple, during famine times.</p>						

						</summary>
